Lost Love\par
By Ambertiger Honorclaw\par
\par
She groped about the room searching for her torch. After finding and lighting it, she hung it up. She thought about something her friend said a few days back.. 'Anyone who has a Khat'sara in the war in the west will receive news of them in three days time', she had said. Upon remembering this information, she bounded down the stairs, forgetting to put on some clothes. She ran down the hall to the front door and looked outside.\par
\par
'It hasn't come yet', she sighed. Looking at herself, her eyes instantly flew open and she shrieked. \par
\par
She cried, 'I must have displayed myself to half the town!' Reaching her room in a hurry, she shut her door and took out a long, slender robe shining a pale green.\par
\par
She said, 'I seem to always reach for this one.. I wonder why?' She didn't have to ask herself that. She knew it comforted her in her Khat'sara's absence. He bought it for her a year after their anniversary, and then it was a bit brighter, but it was still beautiful in her eyes. She proceeded to make herself a small breakfast in her kitchen. After sitting down to eat at the table, a she heard a knock on the door.\par
\par
 She jumped up, hoping it would be the letter telling her everything was all right. After opening it, she received a small amount of shock. A small female Leuian with rather blackish-gray fur was standing at the door. Her eyes sparked with wisdom and her air wasn't that would seem normal. \par
\par
'Mom?!', she cried. \par
\par
'Mina, dear, the older Leuian asked, is everything all right?' After inviting her in, Mina made her some fish sandwiches, her mother's favorite. \par
\par
'You never answered my question dear', her mother said.\par
\par
 After a moment of silence, Mina replied, 'Of course, Mom, why wouldn't it?' Her mother looked down for a moment.. \par
\par
She said, 'I'm sorry, I thought someone told you..' Mina looked at her mother with a face combined with horror and anticipation. \par
\par
She asked hurriedly, 'Told me What?!' \par
\par
Her mother bit her lower lip before she replied, 'Your father.. Didn't make it..' Mina's eyes closed and water began to leak through them. She tried to comfort her mother, whose eyes, too, were beginning to become wet with tears. They hugged each other and continued to talk about the times when Mina's father was still alive.. Until a second knock on the door reminded the young Leuian girl about her own Khat'sara.\par
\par
She told her mother, 'Don't move, Mom, that is probably news about Chad..' She opened the door and a tall, muscular Leuian greeted her. He stood about 7 feet, and was muscular in build, he carried no weapons, so Mina guessed he was a Hand Cleric of Sa, from the marking on his arm. \par
\par
'Are you Chad's Khat'sara?', he asked. Mina nodded. 'Wonderful, I've been trying to find you for hours,' he said with a grin on his face. He handed her a package of letters, about 4 or 5, she guessed. She took them to the table where her mother sat. \par
\par
'Well, apparently, it didn't come because the messenger got lost', she told her mother. She brushed her yellow mane back and put the letters down on the table.  She said, \lquote One from Auntie, another from the bank, one from the High Priestess of Elindale, and ahh.. One from the front in the west..' Her mother told her to open the one from the High Priestess first, as it was probably important business. Mina nodded and pushed the other letters aside. She seemed a little shocked about what she read. 'The High Priestess recently went into the Trance of Prophecy, Mom.. She was heard saying something about an unholy power in the west.. What do you think it could mean, Mom?', she asked.\par
\par
Her mother was just as shocked as she was. "Perhaps Taath's followers are planning a Ritual again?, she offered. \par
\par
Mina replied, 'That doesn't set off the Trance of Prophecy.. The last time the Trance was in effect was when the Demons invaded the islands near here.. If it weren't for the Trance we'd all be dead.' Her mother nodded. Mina sighed and said, 'I guess I should read Auntie's letter, she doesn't write often..' She opened the letter and read it. After giving to her mother she sighed. 'She's coming over again? Wasn't she just here?', she asked her mother.\par
\par
'She is a good khat, and you know it..', her mother replied.\par
\par
'But she always brings that khit.. Last time he was here he broke my vase and ripped one of my robes to shreds..', Mina retorted. Her mother sighed. Mina opened the letter from the back. 'The loan Chad and I got a while back is due.. I think I'm going to have to make some money to pay it off..', said Mina.\par
\par
 'I guess you have to open the one from the front now dear.. You've delayed it long enough.', her mother told her. Mina looked at the last unopened letter on the table and bit her lower lip.\par
\par
 Mina said, 'All right.. I can't delay this any longer, I suppose.' Her arm reached for the letter across the table, her face the full of anxiousness and anticipation.\par
\par
 To Be Continued...\par
