Birth of a Khit\par
By Pacer Snaggletooth\par
\par
He had just finished eating his breakfast. After rinsing out his bowl and placing it back on the shelf, he walked into the bedroom and slipped off his sleeping gown. He reached his paw under the pillow and pulled out his hunting clothes: a forest-green tunic and black leather britches.  He was just pulling on his boots when he heard a knock on the door.\par
\par
He smiled. That must be Idryth, he thought. He and Idryth had made plans that day to hunt in Yelican Forest.  The thought of Idryth always made him smile.  From the first moment he had seen her, she had been the love of his life. And he was her love, her Sir Khat. He half-ran, half-skipped to the door to let her in.\par
\par
It was not Idryth.  There, standing at his door, was a tiny Secian, shivering in the cold. Dewdrops fell off the tips of her wings. She was hardly dressed for a cold February morning, with only a light gown over her shoulders and tiny ruby slippers on her feet.  In her arms, she held a bundle of brightly-colored rags.\par
\par
"Khittiemandus Snaggleteef?" asked the little secian. Khatmandu blinked.  "Issa you Khittiemandus Snaggleteef?" she asked again.\par
\par
"Aye," he began, "how did you know..." but she had already flitted past him into the warmth of his home.\par
\par
"Well, you wassa not gonna leab me stammin out dere in da cold, wassa you?" Khatmandu started to say it wasn't cold, but remembered that Leuians didn't feel the cold like others did.  Even on the coldest of days, their fur kept them warm enough, so that just a light robe would be more than sufficient.\par
\par
The Secian held her bundle of rags even closer to her and let out a sigh. Khatmandu saw her looking over the room as if she were scrutinizing it, searching for something. He looked around, all seemed to be in order to him. It was no different from any other Leuian's home: a fireplace on one wall, with two large chairs facing it, a large eating table in the center of the room, a few shelves with books on one wall and another shelf with his eating dishes on another. He even had a wooden floor; many just had dirt floors. Off to one side of the room was the door leading to his bedroom.\par
\par
"How did you know I was Khatmandu?" he asked.  \par
\par
The Secian smiled. "Words of kind deeds trabel fars wif Secians," she said, and turned her attention to him. "I know you issa good khittie, anna das why I be here todays. I comes to ask for you help."\par
\par
She gently laid her bundle of rags on the table. "Actually, is him dat needs you help." And she pointed to the rags. Khatmandu started as he saw the rags moving on the table. He gasped as the rags fell away a bit and revealed a newborn khit, a tiny ball of orange fur, still wet from the birthing process. \par
\par
"Is he injured?," asked Khatmandu as he pulled back the rags to get a better look at the khit. "Oh no, he issa in perfect comdishun," said the little secian. "He jus needs sombudy to look after him, dat all."\par
\par
"That's all?" chuckled Khatmandu. "Where are his parents?"\par
\par
The secian sighed again. "His poppa issa deaded, anna his momma....."  \par
\par
"His momma.....what?" Khatmandu raised his eyebrow at the secian.\par
\par
The Secian stood silent for a long time. Then very quietly, so quietly, Khatmandu had to lean down to hear her, she said, "His momma no want him. She gonna kill him. She say she don need be tied down wif a baby khittie."\par
\par
"His mother was going to kill him!?!" Khatmandu was astonished. Leuians are fiercely protective of their khits and the thought of a mother wanting to kill or even harm her own, almost made him sick.\par
\par
The secian looked up at Khatmandu, tears in her eyes. "He prolly issa cold. You got a blankie to wrap him in?" Khatmandu blinked, still trying to digest the news of a mother Leuian wanting to harm her khit. He told the Secian to wait there and he walked into his bedroom looking for something to wrap the child in. His quilt was much too large, as Leuian khits are very small at birth, usually only about 12" long from head to toe. He grabbed his sleeping gown and walked back to the Secian. \par
\par
But the Secian was gone. The khit still lay on the table, mewing and cooing. Khatmandu looked out the front door, but saw nothing of the Secian. He walked back to the khit, wrapped him in the gown, lifted the child and went back to the door again. There was no Secian in sight.\par
\par
The khit's little whimpers began growing steadily into a full-blown wail of tears. Khatmandu patted and petted the child, but nothing would stop his crying.  He didn't know what to do with a baby. He had never really been around babies before. What was he supposed to do with this one?  Idryth will know, he thought. But she was late showing up and the khit was screaming even louder now.\par
\par
Finally, in desperation, he wrapped the child tighter in the gown and ran out and down the alley to Tigerclaw and Coeur's home. They had a young khit, Khateul, just four years of age now. They would know how to quiet this child.\par
             \par
***\par
\par
"She what!?!" screamed Coeur when Khatmandu told her of the mother Leuian wanting to kill her own child. "If I ever saw that khat, she....she would be dead!" Coeur spat, furious at the thought of this. "Khat, give me the child. He is hungry." As Coeur stoked the fire to warm the milk, Tigerclaw took Khatmandu aside.\par
\par
"Are you going to keep him?" he asked. "Do I have a choice, Tiger?" Khatmandu replied as he watched Coeur let the khit suck on milk-soaked rags. "What would become of him if I didn't take care of him? I can't just leave him out in the cold to perish. I would be no better than the mother of the child."\par
\par
Tigerclaw nodded. "It's not easy keeping up pace with a growing khit. Believe me, I know," chuckled Tigerclaw as he glanced at his own son trying to get a peek at the baby his mother was holding. Tigerclaw smiled at his friend. "They can be a handful at times, but I guess I wouldn't trade fatherhood in for anything."\par
\par
Khatmandu laughed. "I know it won't be easy to keep up pace with him.  But I'll have to. I always wanted to get khat'sara'd to Idryth and have khits....just didn't know it would come in this order. Idryth!!" Khatmandu gasped. "How can I go hunting with a khit!?! What am I supposed to do with....."\par
\par
Coeur and Tigerclaw exchanged glances, then smiled at Khatmandu. "Life will be different for you now, Khat. Go, find Idryth and tell her. I'm sure she will be pleased. We'll keep an eye on the little Pacer."\par
\par
Khatmandu hugged his friends. He then bent down and kissed the sleeping khit for the first time. Then he ran out the door to find Idryth.\par
\par
***\par
\par
Three days later, Khatmandu stood before the Pride and introduced Pacer Snaggletooth, his son, since it was customary for newborn khits to be taken to the first Pride meeting after their birth and shown to all members. Pacer was welcomed into their family as if he were one of thier own. \par
\par
And all, down to the last khat, swore vengeance on the mother who would have killed her own khit.\par
