\par
Dear Aubrei,\par
\par
I must say that Mom must have been angry at Dad when she chose your name.. Aubrei.  ::shakes his head::  But that is not my point in writing this letter.  Hasn't it been a while since we've spoken?  I cannot believe that I let 100K silvers get in between us, causing this chasm of silence.  Forget the money, because I've forgotten to tell you how important you are to me.\par
\par
Remember the first time we met?  The Circle of Honor Archery contest.  Those were the days, weren't they?  Remember how we beat Skylar and all the other important bow-users, to emerge tied as 5th place (unofficially, because they did not have prizes except for the first three places).  I still remember every moment of that contest, from the crowds of people drawn to the spectacle of the first ever archery contest, and the noise and chatter.  I remember that many had forgotten their entrance fees, and there were many suspicious of others, fearing that thieves might take advantage of that event to pick pocket a few extra silvers.  Do you remember how we met in the Noble's park, but never spoke, because we did not know each other?  I was rather secluded, because the event was filled with the most famous names, and I was standing alone.  I remember the different portals we had to through and the strange arena.  I remember the clown and the stunned creatures that we used as targets.  They never died, did they!?  I remember waiting in anticipation while they called out names, and one by one, the contestants would nock their bluish ash short-bows with the standard arrows, and shoot at the targets.  Did you feel the same anticipation as me when you stood and shot, and after every round, you were chosen to the next?  Do you remember that darned night mosquito, which neither one of us could hit?!  It was that moment, I believe, that we recognized each other.  The past before that event, I hardly remember your face or your charm, but that incident affirmed out kinhood.\par
\par
Do you remember the days back, when we would hunt out rogues and other mischievous critters?  I remember the shades and the screaming and the blood (ours), and the screaming and more screaming.  And the shrieking.  Remember DarkRanger, who we would hunt with, at the thieves' guild?  That long passage through which I know don't even remember.  That was fun, especially when we met the master (of chief?  I even forget the simplest details) assassins, and we were determined to kill it, even for the fun of it, enduring the different fire darts and other spells.  That was fun.\par
\par
Disarming skeletons was always fun, and sometimes, I would serve as a disarming target for you, remember?  I remember the practice sword and the constant surprise I had when you managed to disarm me.  I could have sworn that I held on to the sword with all my might, but you always found a way to distract me.  Silly fool.  And the different useless practice sessions we had, when we would hit each other and use First Aid to heal each other.  Your warms hands and your calming voice was always a comfort, even when I am three years older than you.  Of course, I think my First Aid is better than yours, but it was never apparent because you always seemed to be quicker than me to bandage my wounds up.\par
\par
Then, the medallion, where you spent your entire life savings to buy a Esp aura casting medallion, which you appropriately renamed medallion of the Unknown (or something like that.  Go Elindale).  I always respected you for your devotion to the Unknown, and how you fought for his honor.\par
\par
I remember the first time you mentioned Lorianna, whom you liked.  ::wink wink nudge nudge::  She was a charm.  Perhaps the wedding process has become somewhat banal, and still retaining that high expense, became worthless.  Nevertheless, that was the reason we adopted Rhea (or found out that she was our sister, I never really understood).  You had suggested that I marry her, without the sense to remember that I was the Virgin Bride of Elindale (or so I cause myself to believe).  So, Rhea entered the family and started the entire controversy of Romero-Horawytz-Rashakae, or more commonly known, the RHR's.  Rhea's last name was used first, because she was a lady ("ladies first"), and I was in before yours because I was older.  Thus the RHR's.  Then, it got really hectic as other people whom I did not know began to attach themselves to our family, and got so chaotic that one day, I realize that Araton was part of the family too.  It turned out that he was our family pet or something.  That was possibly the first time that I got angry at everyone, and disowned my last name.  Of course, the anger passed, and I felt ashamed (I never apologized for getting wrathful), and of course, now, I'm Guztymne RHorawytzR.\par
\par
