\pard ============================================================================\par
The First Real Hunt\par
Alihtimasad Asad\par
\par
My name is Alihtimasad Asad, Hithual Sword Cleric of Unknown, the younger brother of Asad the Hithual. My background is something that I wish to avoid discussing for now, as there are too many painful memories and many things still unknown to me.\par
\par
I came to Spur a short while back. I was in awe as to the city\rquote s layout and the wide variety of inhabitants. As a matter of fact, although I don\rquote t like to admit it, I was quite bewildered. I\rquote m accustomed to standing on my own, so the strange new place was a bit of a shock to my mind. So many races, so much diversity. Where should I begin? The sudden realization that I was not quite so independent perturbed me greatly. I now needed help from anyone who would be kind enough to provide it.\par
\par
By good fortune, a more senior Hithual, seeing my confused state, took compassion on me and offered a guiding hand. His name is Rev, Sword Cleric of Odarous. He was very kind to me from the first moment we met, and seemed to take a liking to me quickly.\par
\par
Maybe a day after our first meeting, Rev asked me if I\rquote d like to come on a hunt. Now, I had hunted rogues before in the Training Grounds and a little in Spur\rquote s Rogue Fields. Got a little skill from it, a little coin and food and water. I still couldn\rquote t hit them too often, but their blows did not affect me too much, so I hunted without too much risk. This proposed hunt sounded like something more serious. I inquired where the hunt would be and what we\rquote d be hunting. Rev chuckled and said \ldblquote that lad, will be left as a surprise\rdblquote . So, trusting in my new friend I agreed.\par
\par
Clad only in heavy leather mail and leather helmet, practically without coin, and armed with a used battle axe stripped from a rogue, I followed along. Rev introduced me to Rivet the Hithual. We went to a place nearby, and a search began, looking for a hidden door. This was quite new to me, but I helped. Much to everyone\rquote s surprise, I detected the trap door and we all entered, following Rev. After a bridge, I looked around and found myself in the sewers. \par
\par
This brought back some bad memories for me. I had ventured forth into the sewers of the Training Grounds on numerous occasions. All I could remember was leeches and slimes and slugs and rats, and the occasional rogue. The sting from the rat\rquote s bites and the burn from the slime\rquote s acid was still fresh in my memory. My Leather Mail had been pierced too many times by the sharp teeth of the rats, sometimes attacking 5 at once, and often times almost killing me. Aye, the bitter memory was fresh. I found myself in yet another sewer and remembering my miserable experiences wondered what was to become of me.\par
\par
We seemed to travel for a long time, winding this way and that. The directions were a blur to me, and I knew, that if I were to get lost, there would be little hope for me. Dazed by all the newness, I gripped my battle axe tightly, not knowing what to expect, nor when to expect it. We came to a dead end, I saw no path at all, but Rev being more experienced took us through a chink in the rock. Behold, we have entered the Go-blin Warrens. Now the confusion increased many times. I believe I\rquote d seen a beggar or two of that race, but never met one as friend or foe. I had a feeling in my gut that I was in for some surprises.\par
\par
I gripped the battle axe even more tightly. This new area is dark and dank, with a stench, the likes of which I never imagined. Something feels quite strange about this place. I feel the presence of many, but see only our group. We move along and that feeling becomes more intense. I begin to see tiny eyes peering out from the darkness. I don\rquote t know whether or not to fear, but the tendency is there to be frightened of that not yet experienced. My hand is almost one with the handle of my weapon, I\rquote m gripping so tightly. I secure my shield to my left arm, and check the leather mail and helm. I\rquote ve forgotten to wear these things on occasion and have paid dearly with severe pain. I\rquote m not going to relive that again.\par
\par
Being so new to Spur, I\rquote ve not yet been able to obtain the herbs for increasing my strength and stamina, so I\rquote m still quite weak and very inexperienced. Now I hope that I\rquote ll not be punished for my weakness and killed by those who hide in the darkness. I begin to sweat a little, feeling that dozens of pairs of eyes are watching. I\rquote ve battled two or three rogues at a time, in the past, but something tells me that this will be a long remembered experience. The tension is unbelievable as we look around and wait for the inevitable. \par
\par
All of the sudden, out of the darkness, leap five go-blins, armed with battle axes and sneering at us with their sour little faces. They leaped so fast and hit so hard, that I was instantly knocked down. Taking large damage, lying dazed on the ground, hurt and confused, I feel the touch of Rev upon my chest, healing all of my wounds. His voice says \ldblquote stand lad, and fight hard\rdblquote . I jump to my feet and swing my battle axe at the first go-blin I see. Ahhh, what a feeling, when my weapon connected with his spine and sent a shock up my arm. He had already been hit twice before, and my hit sent him to his death. Rev beams at me and says \ldblquote good work, keep it up!\rdblquote .\par
\par
I look around--five more pairs of beady little eyes, staring at me. I see two of these creatures advance towards me. This time, without hesitation, I attack. Again, my battle axe makes connection. Oh my, what little training I\rquote ve had has paid off. My skill in sharp weaponry is not much more than it was in the Training Grounds, yet I feel that I\rquote ve been given the strength to fight by Unknown. The faith my brethren have in me to bring me along, has given me so much encouragement.\par
\par
The battle becomes furious. I swing my weapon over and over again, becoming exhausted. A red eagle appears over Rev\rquote s head and I feel renewed vigor flow through my body. The axe seems to swing now, as if it has it\rquote s own separate life. I look at my right hand clasping the battle axe and ponder for a moment. I cannot believe that I\rquote m actually hitting these go-blins three or four out of ten swings. The success gives me more strength of mind and I continue to battle on.\par
\par
By now, five have gone to their death, but five more have appeared in their places. What is going on here? Where are they all coming from. The place is small, yet they fill the area. Rev begins to strip the first dead one. The go-blin had on his body a rapier and a battle axe. I am amazed to see two weapons on one creature. Rev calls out \ldblquote Grab the weapons!\rdblquote  I reach out and grab the battle axe, but before I can get to the rapier, a spirit comes from the dead go-blin and grabs it up. The view of this stuns me for a moment, but I\rquote m soon brought back to my senses by the slash of a battle axe to my chest. Oh no! I remember theses spirits from that nasty place in the Training Grounds. That place with the damned shades. How I despise them. I can still remember the sting of the claws of shades and spirits piercing through my mail as if it were no more than a scroll. With that feeling in mind, I begin to sweat more. This one is a cold sweat. I don\rquote t know what to expect next. \par
\par
While I\rquote m remembering my miseries, the spirit claws my head, sending me to my knees. A go-blin takes advantage of the opportunity and sneaks in a good blow with his battle axe. This one sends me down flat on the ground. Stunned and half dead, I see Rev kneel and touch my chest. The force of Odarous heals my mangled body. I leap to my feet and begin to swing at the twisted fellow that sent me to the ground. Rivet instinctively jumps in front of Rev and defends him, while Rev renews his energy. I\rquote ve watched Rivet quietly fighting, but now realize that he sees all that\rquote s going on.\par
\par
Rev swings his sword at the spirit, sending it to the ground. He connects with one swing after the other and the spirit meets it\rquote s end. He strips the spirit and opens the coffer and calls out \ldblquote Get the coins!\rdblquote . I grab for the coins and continue the battle. Rivet continues to battle, intent on the death of all enemies in his path.\par
\par
Rev begins to strip the dead go-blins, one by one. Rivet and I grab for the weapons. I look around and see four spirits now and five go-blins and numerous corpses. Rev begins to take on the spirits single-handedly, while Rivet and I concentrate on the go-blins. They go down, again and again, but it seems as if for each one downed, two more appear. My head reals in astonishment. The battle ensues and I continue to swing my weapon as if by instinct.\par
\par
Swing, by swing, blow by blow, go-blin after go-blin takes damage and goes to meet death. I\rquote m again becoming utterly exhausted with the swinging of my axe. Again, an aura of vigor comes upon me and Rev glances at me and laughs. I\rquote m still so new, I\rquote ve not seen the laying of hands before this night. But, as I fall to the ground again, I feel the hands of my new found mentor upon my chest and hear \ldblquote Stand boy, stand!\rdblquote . I rise up and strengthen my weakened grip upon the handle of my axe and notice that blood now comes from between my fingers from holding the weapon so tightly. My arm feels tired, but my heart carries me onward. The spirit of the battle pushes me to fight on.\par
\par
Now there are ten go-blins attacking, five spirits, corpses lying all around, some beginning to turn to dust. I look around and see a pile of weapons and cloaks from the go-blins. Rivet and I begin to grab at the weapons while trying to keep up what seems to be a futile pace with the fighting. The battle rages on and on and on, with no end in sight. My imagination is staggered by the volume of death here before my eyes. \par
\par
Occasionally Rivet sneers and slaps a go-blin, taunting him. The jovial mood in the midst of a raging battle is nothing I\rquote ve seen before. I\rquote m in a virtual panic, just trying to stay alive, and too shocked with all the action to even feel fright, and he\rquote s teasing them. The sight of this brings a grin to my tightened face and I begin to laugh. \par
\par
With a laugh on my lips, I feel a blow upon my leg which drives me to my knees. Another blow cuts right through my mail leaving a gash on my chest. The laugh ceases as I take on heavy damage. A claw and another axe blow to the head sends me down. Bleeding profusely and close to death, I call out to Rev. This time he\rquote s in the middle of a swing, so I call out to Unknown, nothing happens. I call out again, and a third time. The fog appears over my head and the power that has been sapped from me due to the wounds is revived. By this time Rev has healed my wounds totally and, it\rquote s back to the battle for me. No one has to remind me to stand now. \par
\par
Rev fights on like an inspired one. Odarous must have entered his body for I\rquote ve never imagined that one person could battle spirit after spirit, sometimes five at once, heal the wounded, strip the corpses, open the treasures and command us like a great general. \par
\par
The battle has raged on for two Spurian hours with no sign of ending. Go-blin after go-blin, spirit after spirit, one goes down and another appears, the spirits rising up from the corpses. The go-blins shriek in a deafening manner and more of their kind come to their aid. Some flee in fear for their waning lives while others rush in to attack us.\par
\par
By now, I\rquote m becoming laden with weapons and gold. So much gold, I\rquote ve never seen at one time. The cache of weapons could supply a small army. In my newly formed enthusiasm, I decide to attack a spirit. What a mistake that is, for instead of hitting him, I simply got his attention and he and another came at me. \lquote Twas bad enough to be hit by the go-blins, but the claws of the spirits were quite unwelcome. A claw to the head brings blood to my right eye, obscuring my vision. From my blinded side, the other spirit comes and claws me in the chest, ripping open my mail and my chest along with it. I remember being told earlier to sit if I\rquote m injured, so I do just that. Rev reaches out to heal me, but this time nothing happens. Uncertainty enters my mind. Should I fear now, am I beyond healing? I check and see that I\rquote m severely injured. Again the touch of a hand, and again nothing happens. A third attempt heals me almost totally. By the gods, I am relieved.\par
\par
My strength has not returned to full. I look at Rev and see that he\rquote s haggard now. What is this? He has exchanged his fatigue for my health, what a selfless act. I\rquote ve not yet stood, and Rivet jumps in front of me, taking on the attackers. He yells to me \ldblquote Give vigor to Rev!\rdblquote . Now I remember my position as Cleric of Unknown. With my brethren defending me, I unarm myself and concentrate hard to recall the proper incantation. The runes begin to circle above my head and then rush towards Rev. Rivet calls out, \ldblquote Again! Again!.\rdblquote  I caste again successfully. Rev has not missed a beat, fighting furiously even while close to exhaustion. His trust for his kin is an example for me to learn. Rivet says to me \ldblquote Now, vig yourself!\rdblquote  I do so, and feel the fatigue relieved. I look now at Rev and he\rquote s in perfect health. He beams to me and I feel such delight that for once, I\rquote ve been of some actual use.\par
\par
I think to myself \ldblquote Why not vigor Rivet also?\rdblquote  So I caste at him and another upon myself. He grins at me and nods in thanks, then chuckles. Now I feel as if I\rquote m part of a team, and not simply a liability. I grab my battle axe and jump to my feet, swinging it with a new confidence. My kin look at each other and smile and then look upon me beaming with delight. I feel accepted now, a feeling that is new in my life. And this feeling gives me the hope, that in Spur I may find a future. \par
\par
I look at the spirit that sent me to the ground. He will not live long enough to regret it. I swing harder than ever before and connect with the spirit. The feeling of joy as I send him crashing to the floor. Rev strikes the death blow. I attack the next go-blin and notice Rivet attack him too. I strike once, Rivet strikes the next blow, I strike again, Rivet again, and the go-blin shrieks his last. We move on to the next one. With the sychronized attack, they fall dead at our feet one by one, two by two. The gore is too much to describe, death and mutilation all around us, rivers of blood. Yet in the midst of all this mayhem, a new fighter takes birth. Finally, I\rquote ve found my home amongst kin.\par
\par
Our harnesses and sacks are quite full of weapons and each of us is carrying much coin. My eyes get large when I see how much gold I\rquote m carrying. At this point, every move fatigues us. Rev tells us \ldblquote Time to go, gather all you can and follow up!\rdblquote  Back to the sewers we go. Winding our way through the seeming maze of sewer, we come back to the bridge. \par
\par
Rev then takes us to the trader shop where we begin to sell and sell and sell, for what seems to be quite a long time. At the end of the selling, we are all grinning and beaming with delight. A bit of dancing in celebration of the successful hunt follows. We follow Rev to the bank in Market Circle. Rev says \ldblquote Now we teach Ali how to split the loot from the hunt! Hand all of your coins to him!\rdblquote  Rev and Rivet begin to whisper back and forth. They smile, glance at me and nod to each other. Then, they hand me the gold and silver and I feel honored that they trust me. As I\rquote m preparing to divide things, I see Rev disband the group and the moods of both Rev and Rivet become mischievous. I ask everyone to follow, so I can give them their share of coins. They look at me and laugh, snickering away. I make my request again. They shake their heads no at me. What is this? What are they doing? Is this a joke? I say \ldblquote How do you expect me to divide the plunder if you won\rquote t follow?\rdblquote  Both Rev and Rivet shake their heads again and say in unison \ldblquote This hunt was for you dear kin. Welcome to Spur!\rdblquote\par
