Minstrels And Musings\par
By Esper Lyrian\par
\par
We have some wonderful pieces for you this month, and I hope you'll enjoy them as much as I did.\par
First, we have some poems by Moire and Marigold.\par
\par
Moire's piece is untitled, and she says it was meant in good fun, and not to insult anyone.\par
\par
There's a side I keep hidden\par
There's a side of me I show\par
And sometimes the sides flip-flop\par
And I don't know where to go!\par
\par
There's a plurality to my personality\par
And that's why we call me Ms. Duality.\par
\par
I can be chaste and I can be sexual\par
I can be powerful, sometimes ineffectual.\par
Sometimes I'm happy, and then I'm depressed\par
I feel cursed and I feel blessed\par
\par
There's a plurality to my personality\par
And that's why we call me Ms. Duality.\par
\par
I'm inside and outside, before and after\par
My mind and body are slave and master\par
I am dominant, I am submissive\par
I am black and I'm white\par
I'm jaunty, serious, competent, delerious\par
I'm silent, boisterous,quiescent, roisterous\par
\par
Yes, there's a plurality to my personality\par
And that's why we call me Ms. Duality.\par
(That's me--that's me, too!)\par
\par
